=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining exception handling**\\n\\nI'm considering how signature throws like InstantiationException and IllegalAccessException work. If a constructor throws a RuntimeException, it seems like it propagates the error. It's good that it catches Exceptions, including RuntimeExceptions. Now, looking at the provider branch, it seems that in a native context, the exception is okay, and it may log an error using a simple logger for prints. I think testing shouldn't present any issues.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated the `ThreadContext` coverage test to reach the remaining `Class#newInstance()` call sites.\n\nChanged files:\n- `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-api/2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_logging_log4j/log4j_api/ThreadContextTest.java`\n- `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-api/2.0/src/test/resources/log4j2.component.properties`\n- `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-api/2.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/log4j-provider.properties`\n\nWhat changed:\n- Added public nested `ThreadContextMap` implementations used through Log4j’s normal configuration mechanism.\n- Configured `log4j2.threadContextMap` to a map whose public no-arg constructor is invoked and then fails, exercising `ThreadContext.init(...)` line 220.\n- Configured the Log4j provider resource with a working provider `ThreadContextMap`, exercising `ThreadContext.init(...)` line 237.\n- The test asserts normal public `ThreadContext` map and stack behavior after the supported fallback to the provider map.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a04868bc46b7298016a40af0f03c4819594f48be2f2f7f8cf\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 681, "output": 1622, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51455, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782623997051, "responseId": "resp_0a04868bc46b7298016a40aefdc3888195a2f3133804506828"}}
